headline: Hartford (HIG): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q1 Earnings?
summary: Hartford has followed the market’s trajectory closely, rising in tandem with the S&P 500 over the past six months. The stock has climbed by 8.2% to $121.22 per share while the index has gained 4.1%.
